headline: In stagnant job market, worker sentiment 'is taking a hit'
summary: Workers are feeling crummy about their jobs, according to private payroll processor ADP, a sour sentiment that has been on an "unprecedented six-month run of weakness" amid a stagnant labor market.

headline: ADP National Employment Report Preliminary Estimate for January 31, 2026
summary: For the four weeks ending January 31, 2026, U.S. private employers added an average of 10,250 jobs per week, according to the NER Pulse, a weekly update of the monthly ADP National Employment Report (NER).

headline: Gold Falls Below $5,000 in Thin Trade
summary: Gold prices slipped back below $5,000 in thin trading, with much of Asia closed for the Lunar New Year and U.S. markets shut on Monday. Futures in New York fell 2.2% to $4,937.40 a troy ounce. "Liquidity conditions remain thin, particularly across metals," Sucden Financial analysts said.
